EXACT UUID-SCAN ALGORITHM (validated; dry-run feedback asked for it verbatim). Insert in ticket-transition.sh archived->open arm, before exec'ing ticket-revert.sh:
archived_uuid=$(python3 - "$TRACKER_DIR/$ticket_id" <<'PYEOF'
import json, os, sys
tdir = sys.argv[1]
archived, reverted = {}, set()
for fname in os.listdir(tdir):
    if fname.startswith('.') or not fname.endswith('.json'):
        continue
    try:
        with open(os.path.join(tdir, fname), encoding='utf-8') as f:
            ev = json.load(f)
    except Exception:
        continue
    et = ev.get('event_type')
    if et == 'ARCHIVED':
        archived[ev.get('uuid', '')] = ev.get('timestamp', 0)
    elif et == 'REVERT':
        t = ev.get('data', {}).get('target_event_uuid', '')
        if t:
            reverted.add(t)
live = [(ts, u) for u, ts in archived.items() if u and u not in reverted]
if live:
    print(max(live)[1])
PYEOF
) || archived_uuid=""
If empty -> error "no live ARCHIVED event (status may be stale)", exit 1. Otherwise exec bash "$SCRIPT_DIR/ticket-revert.sh" "$ticket_id" "$archived_uuid" --reason="un-archive via transition archived open".
